Transfer of funds on account ceasing to be Saving Gateway Account
	Transfer of funds on account ceasing to be Saving Gateway account
		This section applies to an account which ceases to be a Saving Gatewayaccount by virtue of regulations under section 10.
		Regulations may make provision about—
			the circumstances in which the funds in the account may be transferred toan investment plan of a kind prescribed by regulations, and
			the procedure to be followed on a transfer.
		Regulations may, in particular—
			require a person who is or was an approved account provider, on a requestby the account holder, to issue a certificate to the account holder;
			prescribe the period within which the certificate is to be issued;
			prescribe the information to be included in the certificate;
			require the account holder to present the certificate to the provider ofthe investment plan to which the funds are to be transferred;
			require the provider of the plan to produce the certificate in prescribedcircumstances.
